<H1><A HREF="../">Closest Pair Data Structures</A>:
Applications</H1>

The following algorithms and applications can be implemented efficiently
using our new closest pair data structures, or involve closest pair
computation as important subroutines.

<UL>
<LI>Dynamic minimum spanning trees
<LI>Two-optimization heuristics in combinatorial optimization
<LI><A HREF="http://compgeom.cs.uiuc.edu/~jeffe/open/skeleton.html">Straight skeletons and roof design</A>
<LI><A HREF="RayDiagram/">Ray-intersection diagram</A>
<LI>Other collision detection applications
<LI>Hierarchical clustering
<LI>Traveling salesman heuristics
<LI>Greedy matching
<LI>Constructive induction
<LI>Gr&ouml;bner bases
</UL>

<P><HR>
<A HREF="/~eppstein/">David Eppstein,
